abstract: Only two of the four Republicans whose support would be needed to call witnesses have signaled they will support it.
snippet: Only two of the four Republicans whose support would be needed to call witnesses have signaled they will support it.
lead_paragraph: The leak of a book manuscript written by John R. Bolton, President Trump’s former national security adviser, has rocked Mr. Trump’s impeachment trial and increased pressure on Republicans to call Mr. Bolton as a witness.

headline_main: After Bolton leak, the Senate math on witnesses is unchanged — for now.

abstract: The new policy revised the so-called public charge rule, making immigrants ineligible for permanent legal status if they use public benefits like Medicaid and food stamps.
snippet: The new policy revised the so-called public charge rule, making immigrants ineligible for permanent legal status if they use public benefits like Medicaid and food stamps.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Supreme Court on Monday allowed the Trump administration to move forward with plans to deny green cards to immigrants who are thought to be likely to make even occasional and minor use of public benefits like Medicaid, food stamps and housing vouchers.

abstract: President Trump asserted that Democrats had not asked the former national security adviser to testify.
snippet: President Trump asserted that Democrats had not asked the former national security adviser to testify.
lead_paragraph: President Trump falsely tweeted this morning that House Democrats didn’t seek testimony from John R. Bolton, his former national security adviser.
headline_main: Fact check: The House did ask Bolton to testify.

abstract: Ken Starr is urged to be a little less Atticus Finch and a little more Miss Universe.
snippet: Ken Starr is urged to be a little less Atticus Finch and a little more Miss Universe.
lead_paragraph: Warming up the Senate on Monday, one of President Trump’s lawyers, Jay Sekulow, promised the defense team would move in a manner “expeditious but yet thorough.” But even some of the president’s most enthusiastic supporters seem to have concluded that Ken Starr, the former independent counsel turned presidential defense attorney, failed to live up the bill.
headline_main: Starr manages to unite the left and the right — in boredom.

abstract: “I’m not taking a side, Chris,” Katie Pavlich retorted, before Bret Baier cut in and changed the topic.
snippet: “I’m not taking a side, Chris,” Katie Pavlich retorted, before Bret Baier cut in and changed the topic.
lead_paragraph: Chris Wallace, the “Fox News Sunday” anchor, got into a heated exchange with an on-air colleague, Katie Pavlich, shortly before the Senate trial resumed on Monday, at one point telling her, “Get your facts straight.”
headline_main: Fox anchor warns colleague to ‘tone it down’ in argument over trial.

abstract: Ms. White, who recently joined the Trump administration as a religious adviser, said her remarks referred to a Bible passage.
snippet: Ms. White, who recently joined the Trump administration as a religious adviser, said her remarks referred to a Bible passage.
lead_paragraph: Paula White, a Florida televangelist and religious adviser to President Trump, defended herself Sunday after a video circulated online of her calling for the miscarriage of “satanic pregnancies,” language that she said was taken out of context by critics.

abstract: Sounding more like a college professor than a fierce legal advocate, Ken Starr walked senators through the history of impeachment.
snippet: Sounding more like a college professor than a fierce legal advocate, Ken Starr walked senators through the history of impeachment.
lead_paragraph: Ken Starr, the independent counsel in the impeachment case of former President Bill Clinton, got the second day of President Trump’s defense off to a historical start as the White House legal team ignored revelations from a book manuscript by John R. Bolton, the former national security adviser.

abstract: The president plans tariffs on metal items like nails and cables after his earlier move raised the cost of making those products in the United States.
snippet: The president plans tariffs on metal items like nails and cables after his earlier move raised the cost of making those products in the United States.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump has announced plans to broaden his tariffs on foreign steel and aluminum, saying the existing tariffs had not proved as effective as he had hoped in reviving American production.

abstract: The majority leader urged his Republican colleagues not to rush to any conclusions after Bolton’s revelations.
snippet: The majority leader urged his Republican colleagues not to rush to any conclusions after Bolton’s revelations.
lead_paragraph: John R. Bolton was the only topic on the minds of Republicans as they huddled behind closed doors on Monday for a luncheon just before the impeachment trial began. But Senator Mitch McConnell, Republican of Kentucky and the majority leader, urged his colleagues not to rush to any conclusions.

abstract: California lawyer Michael Avenatti stood to greet 120 prospective jurors who came to a New York courtroom Monday to fill out questionnaires for his trial on charges he tried to extort millions of dollars from Nike.
snippet: California lawyer Michael Avenatti stood to greet 120 prospective jurors who came to a New York courtroom Monday to fill out questionnaires for his trial on charges he tried to extort millions of dollars from Nike.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — California lawyer Michael Avenatti stood to greet 120 prospective jurors who came to a New York courtroom Monday to fill out questionnaires for his trial on charges he tried to extort millions of dollars from Nike.
headline_main: Avenatti Greets Prospective Jurors for Extortion Trial
